# Installer image with kali-linux-everything
#
# But that image is not really useful, see:
# https://gitlab.com/kalilinux/internal/roadmap/-/issues/363#note_649803259
#
# ./build.sh --installer --variant everything

## Metapackages
# You can customize the set of Kali metapackages (groups of tools)
# available in the installer ISO
# For the complete list see: https://www.kali.org/tools/kali-meta/
kali-linux-core
kali-tools-top10
kali-linux-default
kali-linux-large
kali-linux-everything

## Graphical desktops
kali-desktop-xfce
kali-desktop-gnome
kali-desktop-kde
